==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[αβουλια]], from [[α-]] + [[βουλη]] ‘will’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ə'bu:lɪə/

===Noun===
'''aboulia'''
# absence of will-power or decisiveness, especially as a symptom of mental illness
#:''He felt without volition, plunged into a state of '''aboulia'''.''  (Fowles, ''The French Lieutenant's Woman'')